## Verification Plan

### Build verification
```bash
# baseline still builds
make cudart && ./cudart > /dev/null

# accelerated builds
mkdir -p build && cd build
cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
make -j4
./rt_accel > /dev/null
```

### Correctness check
- Both renderers write PPM output; visually compare (same scene, different sample counts)
- Image should not be all-black, all-NaN, or exhibit fireflies worse than baseline

### Benchmark run
```bash
chmod +x benchmark.sh
./benchmark.sh
cat benchmark_results.csv
```

### Profiling
```bash
# FP64 leak check — should be 0 after fixes
ncu --metrics smsp__sass_thread_inst_executed_op_dfma_pred_on.sum ./build/rt_accel > /dev/null

# Warp efficiency — should improve post-wavefront
ncu --metrics smsp__thread_inst_executed_per_inst_executed.ratio ./build/rt_accel > /dev/null
```

---

## Expected Speedup Table (from IMPLEMENTATION_GUIDE)

| Configuration | ~Time (1200×800, 32 spp) |
|---|---|
| Baseline CUDA (ch12, naive) | ~7 s |
| + FP64 fixes only | ~6 s |
| + LBVH | ~2–3 s |
| + Wavefront | ~1–2 s |
| + OIDN (32spp → ~256spp quality) | +0.02 s |
| + Multi-GPU (if 2× available) | ~0.5–1 s |

Benchmark script will measure actual values on your hardware.
